        public static <E,R> org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<java.lang.Object> okOr400(Either<E,R> body)
        Creates a new response with the supplied body; if the body is a right value the response will be a 200, otherwise a 400.
        Parameters:
        body - either the content of a 200 (right value) or an error to output in the body of a 400.
        Returns:
        the response entity.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the argument is null.

      • okOr400

        public static <E,R> org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<java.lang.Object> okOr400(java.util.function.Supplier<Either<E,R>> errorOrResult)
        Creates a new response with the supplied body; if the body is a right value the response will be a 200, otherwise a 400.
        Parameters:
        errorOrResult - the response body producer. The produced body can either be the content of a 200 (right value) or an error to output in the body of a 400.
        Returns:
        the response entity.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the supplier is null or the Either value produced by the supplier is null.

      • _400

        @SafeVarargs
public static <T> org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<T> _400(T... body)
        Creates a new 400 response with an optional body. If called with no arguments as in _400(), the response will have an empty body; if a body argument is given, it will be written to the response body using the configured Spring MVC message converters.
        Parameters:
        body - optional response body.
        Returns:
        a new 400 response.
